         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1350">
               <p>Little is known of this eccentric figure, who called himself &apos;John-Baptist
                  the Arch Teacher&apos; beyond what is conveyed in his extended set of
                  advertisements and letters against the early Methodists, and particularly their
                  leaders <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2221.xml"/>Whitefield</persName> and
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>. In the
                     mid-<date>1760s</date> he also attempted to claim a Parliamentary prize for
                  establishing a means of ascertaining longitude in navigation, by appeal to
                  passages in Matthew and Mark.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
